messages.content: ComfyUI-RAVE is an unofficial ComfyUI implementation of RAVE, which uses BlenderNeko's Unsampler for noise inversion. It includes a basic workflow using the cupcake train example from the RAVE paper.
What is BlenderNeko's Unsampler used for in ComfyUI-RAVE?
BlenderNeko's Unsampler is used for noise inversion in ComfyUI-RAVE.
What example is included in the basic workflow of ComfyUI-RAVE?
The cupcake train example, taken from the RAVE paper, is included in the basic workflow of ComfyUI-RAVE.
Which version of stable diffusion was ComfyUI-RAVE mostly tested with?
ComfyUI-RAVE was mostly tested with SD1.5, although SDXL does work as well, but potentially not as well as SD1.5.
What might be the reason for SDXL not working as well as SD1.5 with ComfyUI-RAVE?
The multi-resolution training in SDXL might reduce the tiling effect, which could be the reason why it doesn't work as well as SD1.5 with ComfyUI-RAVE.
Can ComfyUI-RAVE be used with the SDXL model?
Yes, ComfyUI-RAVE can be used with the SDXL model, although it might not work as well as with the SD1.5 model due to the multi-resolution training reducing the tiling effect.
